<H3>
What's A Microprocessor?</H3>

<UL>
<LI>
Refresher: vacuum tubes, transistors, computer arithmetic; the 6-gate XOR
and binary adder</LI>

<LI>
NPN transistors, the silicon sandwich and wire routing, feature size</LI>

<LI>
Parts of a microprocessor: instruction decoder, ALU, memory interface</LI>

<LI>
Cost vs. price; smaller is cheaper is faster is cooler is more reliable...where
does it stop?</LI>

<LI>
Is there any task microprocessors <I>can't</I> do?</LI>

<LI>
Are microprocessors really ubiquitous?&nbsp; What are some examples?&nbsp;
(Digital watch; calculator; smartcard; car; most electronic appliances;
pagers;</LI>
</UL>

