<h1>Discussion: Computing for the Masses</h1>

<h3>From Transistors to Logic Gates (demo/tutorial)</h3>

<ul>
  <li> The "water pipe" analogy for transistors
  <li> Simple logic gates and truth tables
  <li> Compound logic functions
  <li> Combinational circuits, and how to make a BCD-to-seven-segment
       decoder
</ul>

<h3>Integrated Circuits and the Microprocessor</h3>

<ul>
  <li> What's the significance of the microprocessor....
       <ul>
         <li> technically?
         <li> commercially?
         <li> socially?
       </ul>
  <li> What do you think about the
       "Gutenberg comparison" in the <i>Microprocessor Renaissance</i>
       article?
  <li> Intel's dominance: Luck? Talent? Both?
  <li> <A
       HREF="http://www.intel.com/intel/museum/25anniv/html/hof/techspecs.htm">
       Killer stats</A> on Intel processors
  <li> Do you think Moore's Law will ever stop being valid?
</ul>

<h3>Attack of the Killer Micros</h3>
<ul>
  <li> First micros: Altair, and Apple I.  Why didn't they sell (except
       to a few hobbyists)?  (Pictures of <A
       HREF="http://wwwcsif.cs.ucdavis.edu/~csclub/museum/items/altair_8800_apple_1.html">Altair 800 and Apple I</A>,  and the <A
       HREF="http://www.navi.net/apple/homebrew.html">Apple I motherboard</A>)
  <li> Why did Woz use the 6502 microprocessor, instead of an Intel CPU?
  <li> Killer Apps: what was it for Big Iron?  the Apple II?  The Macintosh?
       Is there a new 
       "Killer App" today, and if so what is it helping to sell?
  <li> Preview: Convergence...
</ul>


