<h3>Computer evolution: Integrated Circuits and the Microprocessor</h3>
d21 7
a27 17
  <li> Original Silicon Valley; Fairchild, Shockley; entrepreneurial
       spirit of spinning off a company.  Has this happened recently?
       (Sunsoft -> Marimba; HP -> Apple)
  <li> Intel dominance: Luck? Talent? Both?
  <li> What's the significance of the microprocessor?  (General purpose
       computer-on-a-chip)  Contrast: how to build computers before?
       Used various logic gates, etc.
  <li> Impact of microprocessor on markets? (Uniformization; encourage
       convergence 
       to small number of standards; made it affordable to build micros)
  <li> Why "the invention of 500 years"?
       Because enables computers to
       penetrate everywhere: <i>universality</i> and <i>compactness</i>.
       (Examples: today's car has XXX computers in
       it, about XXX times the computational power of a mainframe from
       the 70s).
